The paper deals with the problem of tracking and control of Gauss-Markov processes over erasure-prone links, which involves information theory, control theory, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MA (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of variable-length coding techniques, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and the paper also mentions the use of the linear quadratic Gaussian control, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
